The global herbal tea market is segmented based on type, packaging, and distribution channel. In terms of type, different varieties such as green tea, black tea, chamomile tea, peppermint tea, and others are popular among consumers. The packaging segment includes options like loose tea, tea bags, and bottled tea, catering to varying preferences and convenience needs. Moreover, the distribution channel plays a crucial role in reaching consumers, with supermarkets/hypermarkets, convenience stores, and online retail channels all contributing significantly to the herbal tea market's growth.

